title: Mary Dawson Earns #ASunWGolf Player of the Week Honor
text: Mary Dawson Earns #ASunWGolf Player of the Week Honor Story Links Mary Dawson set two program records en route to her first-ever Atlantic Sun Women's Golfer of the Week award, announced Thursday by the league office.Dawson opened play at the Pinehurst Challenge with a four-under par 68, which set the program 18-hole record before she added back-to-back scorecards of 72 to finish in a tie for seventh out of 104 golfers. The senior from Melbourne, Fla. finished with a three-round total of 212 setting the program record in the process. With Dawson's record-setting weekend, North Florida finished in eighth place including a program record low tournament score of 877 as well as the second lowest single round score of 287. The Ospreys return to action at the Betsy Rawls Longhorn Invitational from Oct. 20-21 in Austin, Texas.This marks the third time this season an UNF women's golfer has earned a weekly award from the Atlantic Sun Conference. Atlantic Sun Women's Golfer of the Week - Oct. 15th
